1
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,050
[Episode 30]

3
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:44,140
All you do is eat.

4
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,030
You were brought into the task force

5
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:46,150
to investigate cases.

6
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:47,140
I haven't eaten yet.

7
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:47,870
Last bite.

8
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:48,650
Hurry up.

9
00:01:48,780 --> 00:01:49,710
Check the files.

10
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:00,930
Here.

11
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:04,050
Ju,

12
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:04,670
is

13
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,220
Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company

14
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:07,640
related to our case?

15
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,770
It will be if we find something.

16
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:12,520
I've read these Mazhi County files

17
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,620
several times.

18
00:02:14,170 --> 00:02:15,870
If I can really find a clue,

19
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,810
my plan to transfer
to the Criminal Investigation Detachment

20
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:20,360
will succeed sooner.

21
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:21,960
You...

22
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,710
Why is a kid like you

23
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:25,100
so calculating now?

24
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:25,880
If that's how you think,

25
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,710
you should just go back.

26
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:27,660
No, no, no.

27
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:28,740
I'm happy

28
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,870
that you're making me work.

29
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:31,110
It's good training.

30
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:32,560
My dream

31
00:02:32,579 --> 00:02:33,280
is to become a police officer

32
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,800
like you.

33
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,480
Then I can boss young people around

34
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,480
and not let them finish their meals.

35
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:43,110
So resentful.

36
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,710
Ju.

37
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:52,470
Is this it?

38
00:02:58,829 --> 00:03:00,560
It's a gasoline ration ticket.

39
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:03,750
It seems Li Yongqiang's

40
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,470
Hongyuan Freight Company

41
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:07,250
might be related

42
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:08,310
to the Duojie case.

43
00:03:09,810 --> 00:03:11,080
The employee list for Hongyuan Freight

44
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,140
has been uploaded.

45
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:13,370
But the page numbers are wrong.

46
00:03:13,370 --> 00:03:14,680
Some are missing in the middle.

47
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,520
Everyone, go through

48
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,410
what we have first

49
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:17,780
and pick the key targets to investigate.

50
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:18,579
Yes, Captain.

51
00:03:19,829 --> 00:03:20,540
Get to work.

52
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,410
Ju,

53
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:29,329
the one on your screen

54
00:03:29,329 --> 00:03:30,790
looks like an accountant,

55
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,079
not a truck driver.

56
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:34,730
Are you here to read someone's face?

57
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:38,530
Ju.

58
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:39,750
Ju.

59
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,500
What now?

60
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,450
Look at this one.

61
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,730
Looks just like a truck driver.

62
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:45,660
That's true.

63
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:52,740
Wait.

64
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:53,480
Go back.

65
00:03:56,030 --> 00:03:59,890
[Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company]
[Employee Personal Information Form]

66
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,170
Wu Jiang.

67
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:03,710
Our company's Vice President, Wu Jiang,

68
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:04,840
outranks Bai Chun,

69
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,430
but he's stuck managing Mine No. 2.

70
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,810
So he always causes trouble for Bai Chun.

71
00:04:09,810 --> 00:04:11,120
I called him out on it a few times,

72
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,850
and now he holds a grudge against me, too.

73
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:14,650
The one who filed
that false report last time

74
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:15,910
was probably Wu Jiang.

75
00:04:23,010 --> 00:04:28,170
♪ You are my deepest love ♪

76
00:04:28,370 --> 00:04:29,500
Wu, stop singing!

77
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:30,980
♪ Just like a snow mountain ♪

78
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:31,570
Forget the snow mountain!

79
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:32,240
Come on, come on!

80
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:32,720
Cheers!

81
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:33,740
Come on, cheers!

82
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,070
Cheers!

83
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,120
Who skipped the song?

84
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,710
I did. I did, Mr. Wu.

85
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,659
I'm really sorry, Mr. Wu.

86
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,000
These 2 police officers

87
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,100
are here to see you.

88
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:45,460
Officers.

89
00:04:46,010 --> 00:04:46,800
I'm sorry.

90
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,250
What is it?

91
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,360
Wu Jiang, right?

92
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,590
We are
from the Municipal Public Security Bureau.

93
00:04:52,590 --> 00:04:53,590
We have something

94
00:04:53,770 --> 00:04:54,930
to ask you.

95
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:58,390
Sure.

96
00:04:59,250 --> 00:04:59,720
Sure.

97
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,180
Mr. Wu, you've been

98
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,140
very successful these past few years.

99
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:06,200
From Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company

100
00:05:06,270 --> 00:05:08,400
to Vice President of Xinhai Coal Mine.

101
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:10,930
Yes.

102
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:13,160
Officers,

103
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,850
you know quite a lot about me.

104
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,330
It's been over 10 years.

105
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:17,880
I was young back then.

106
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:19,790
I joined a convoy just to get by.

107
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:21,020
Back then,

108
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,350
at the freight company,

109
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:23,740
what was your job?

110
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,040
Back then...

111
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:28,070
I was just a driver.

112
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,180
Driving trucks and hauling goods.

113
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:33,580
The east route, to the provincial capital.

114
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,860
Do you know County Mayor Duojie?

115
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:38,620
I was just a driver.

116
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:39,740
How would I have the chance

117
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:41,000
to know a county mayor?

118
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:42,380
Besides,

119
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:43,380
I can't really tell

120
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:44,909
those Tibetan names apart.

121
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:47,100
Like Duoji, Sangjie...

122
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,620
Their names make my head spin.

123
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:50,740
Seventeen years ago,

124
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:52,600
something big happened in Mazhi.

125
00:05:52,690 --> 00:05:54,390
County Mayor Duojie went missing.

126
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:55,320
Do you know that?

127
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:57,950
I think I heard about it.

128
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:00,040
During the days

129
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:00,800
of County Mayor Duojie's incident,

130
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,750
what were you doing?

131
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,740
Can you recall?

132
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,160
That question

133
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,860
is a bit too hard to answer.

134
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,870
It was over 10 years ago.

135
00:06:07,890 --> 00:06:09,550
How am I supposed to remember?

136
00:06:11,010 --> 00:06:11,810
For us,

137
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,140
every day was the same.

138
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:14,810
Just hauling goods,

139
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,120
driving,

140
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:17,740
and pulling all-nighters.

141
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:20,290
Then do you know Li Yongqiang?

142
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:27,800
Li Yongqiang?

143
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,130
Doesn't ring a bell.

144
00:06:40,409 --> 00:06:41,740
Does he have a nickname?

145
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:43,120
A nickname?

146
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,250
Yeah.

147
00:06:45,330 --> 00:06:46,250
Back then,

148
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,930
we didn't really know
each other's full names.

149
00:06:47,930 --> 00:06:48,990
We used nicknames.

150
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,150
I remember there was one guy,

151
00:06:51,150 --> 00:06:52,200
called Moneybag.

152
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:53,930
He wore a watch on every trip.

153
00:06:54,150 --> 00:06:55,220
Later, we found out

154
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,570
that his watch was broken.

155
00:06:56,570 --> 00:06:58,170
The hands didn't move at all.

156
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:00,730
There was also one called Monkey.

157
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:01,720
And then there was

158
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,420
Zhang,

159
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:03,270
Wang,

160
00:07:04,010 --> 00:07:04,560
and Wu.

161
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:05,860
Wu Jiang,

162
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,310
let me remind you.

163
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:08,770
Li Yongqiang

164
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:10,210
was Hongyuan Freight Company's

165
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:11,540
legal representative.

166
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,830
Oh, you mean the boss?

167
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,350
I was just a driver.

168
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:15,880
How would I

169
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,050
know the boss?

170
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:18,830
I only know one big shot—

171
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,120
our fleet captain.

172
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:21,530
Then when did you

173
00:07:21,530 --> 00:07:23,390
leave Hongyuan Freight Company?

174
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:25,970
1996...

175
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:28,670
1997, I think.

176
00:07:29,610 --> 00:07:31,050
I didn't leave by choice.

177
00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:32,390
The fleet captain

178
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,460
told us one day

179
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,450
that the company went bust

180
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,880
and not to come back.

181
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:37,630
He gave us

182
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:38,200
a month's wages

183
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,330
and told us to leave.

184
00:07:42,740 --> 00:07:44,540
Just like that, we were unemployed.

185
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,310
Do you know

186
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:46,220
why this freight company

187
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:47,220
got into trouble?

188
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:49,220
I don't know.

189
00:07:50,130 --> 00:07:51,820
Because your boss, Li Yongqiang,

190
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,880
was involved in illegal gold mining.

191
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:59,030
Is that so?

192
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:01,220
This incident

193
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:02,590
was a pretty big deal

194
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,140
in Mazhi County back then.

195
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:05,620
You never heard about it?

196
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:08,620
No.

197
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:12,180
Those years were tough.

198
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,270
Nothing went right.

199
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,820
Besides, there's a lot

200
00:08:16,130 --> 00:08:17,590
I can't remember clearly.

201
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:19,620
I don't care to look back.

202
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:24,910
Take care, you two.

203
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,460
He was a bit too talkative.

204
00:08:32,429 --> 00:08:33,220
You also suspect

205
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,820
he wasn't telling the truth?

206
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,100
But his story

207
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,330
basically lines up

208
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,500
with what we know.

209
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,409
There are no obvious holes.

210
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:41,549
That actually

211
00:08:41,570 --> 00:08:43,030
makes it more suspicious.

212
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:44,410
Exactly.

213
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,010
When someone is lying,

214
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:47,890
to make it look like

215
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:49,420
they're telling the truth,

216
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:50,830
they tend to add

217
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,260
a lot of trivial details.

218
00:08:53,210 --> 00:08:53,850
Like

219
00:08:55,290 --> 00:08:57,150
the Moneybag, the Monkey,

220
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,250
the broken watch, and so on.

221
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:00,410
To flesh out the lie

222
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,770
as much as possible

223
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:03,380
and make it seem real.

224
00:09:04,570 --> 00:09:05,240
There's one more thing

225
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,300
I can't figure out.

226
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:10,110
In the pocket of the skeleton's pants,

227
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:12,710
why was there a gasoline ration ticket?

228
00:09:12,710 --> 00:09:14,840
Back then, Li Yongqiang was shot dead,

229
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,720
and Qima'er Gold Mine was closed.

230
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:18,530
With Hongyuan Freight Company

231
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:19,290
serving as Li Yongqiang's

232
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:20,370
front organization,

233
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,050
why would his employees

234
00:09:21,050 --> 00:09:22,290
have any reason

235
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,780
to kill Captain Duojie?

236
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,930
And even left evidence

237
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:28,810
on the Captain's body?

238
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:31,870
It makes no sense.

239
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,360
It doesn't add up.

240
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:39,990
Keep investigating.

241
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:42,260
Find everyone we can at Hongyuan

242
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,420
and check them one by one.

243
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:48,360
Since Chenlong Coal Mine was merged,

244
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,000
Manager Wu has been in charge.

245
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,580
There isn't enough
dust suppression equipment,

246
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:52,890
and he only cares about mining coal.

247
00:09:52,890 --> 00:09:53,790
The dust is so thick

248
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:55,320
that it is like a sandstorm.

249
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:56,860
The Chairman said

250
00:09:56,860 --> 00:09:58,410
the city is focusing on rectification,

251
00:09:58,410 --> 00:09:59,670
so there might be spot checks anytime.

252
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:00,530
Mr. Meng,

253
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:01,500
should we ask Manager Bai

254
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,500
to lend us some staff and equipment?

255
00:10:05,150 --> 00:10:06,650
Next time you come here,

256
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:08,070
clean yourself up first.

257
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:11,780
Mr. Meng,

258
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:13,030
this door of yours

259
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:14,290
isn't of good quality.

260
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:14,890
I'll ask General Affairs

261
00:10:14,890 --> 00:10:16,090
to replace it for you.

262
00:10:21,090 --> 00:10:21,590
No need.

263
00:10:22,730 --> 00:10:24,060
You can get off work now.

264
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,500
Hello.

265
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:32,620
They've investigated Wu Jiang?

266
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:35,750
What did they ask?

267
00:10:47,570 --> 00:10:48,300
Here, let me.

268
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:51,250
I'll go air out

269
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:52,440
Uncle's blanket.

270
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:53,710
Zhacuo

271
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,720
really doesn't know
how to take care of others.

272
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,520
Don't bother.

273
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:58,240
It's getting dark soon.

274
00:10:58,340 --> 00:10:59,800
I'll remind Zhacuo later.

275
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,410
Has Shao gone back
to the provincial capital?

276
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,620
How would I know?

277
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:10,700
Actually, Shao

278
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,230
has always cared about you.

279
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:14,750
You don't need to say that.

280
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,820
I'll go air out the blanket.

281
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:21,480
Bai.

282
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:27,690
Is this magazine still in print?

283
00:11:27,980 --> 00:11:28,710
My child likes it,

284
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:30,440
so I've kept the subscription.

285
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:32,890
Your child must be in the eighth grade,
right?

286
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:33,820
How are his studies?

287
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:34,700
Much better than mine.

288
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:35,900
Especially English.

289
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:40,740
He'll transfer to Chengdu next semester.

290
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,730
The educational resources
are better there.

291
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,460
I'm going to Chengdu, too.

292
00:11:47,570 --> 00:11:48,570
I'm leaving soon.

293
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:54,360
I'm giving the supermarket
to my brother-in-law.

294
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:56,120
The money to open it

295
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:58,220
came from my father-in-law anyway.

296
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:12,640
I'm sorry.

297
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:15,200
I'm being a deserter again.

298
00:12:16,570 --> 00:12:18,030
You don't need to say that.

299
00:12:19,330 --> 00:12:21,550
Roads are better curved,
and bows better bent.

300
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:24,170
Words are better straight,
and arrows better sent.

301
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:24,740
It's okay.

302
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:25,790
That's the truth.

303
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:28,610
Back in the Uninhabited Zone,

304
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:31,000
the environment was so harsh.

305
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:34,740
That's why you got sick.

306
00:12:35,940 --> 00:12:37,030
Going to a place with a lower altitude

307
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,360
is the right thing to do.

308
00:12:40,430 --> 00:12:41,780
If you told me at any time

309
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,200
that you wanted to leave,

310
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,400
I could understand.

311
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:48,180
But why must it be today?

312
00:12:49,430 --> 00:12:50,650
Why now?

313
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,230
Just when the remains have been found?

314
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:55,130
But why did those remains

315
00:12:55,130 --> 00:12:56,750
appear there?

316
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:57,550
What exactly did the Captain

317
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:58,740
go through back then?

318
00:12:58,740 --> 00:12:59,750
Who was behind it?

319
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:00,890
None of these things

320
00:13:00,890 --> 00:13:02,340
have been cleared up yet.

321
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:04,330
Because

322
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,960
the remains have been found,

323
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:07,390
I feel like I can finally

324
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:08,300
leave.

325
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:10,440
For years, it felt like a hand

326
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,210
was tightly

327
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,300
gripping my heart.

328
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:13,720
Every day I stayed in Mazhi,

329
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,910
I felt like that.

330
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:16,290
Do you understand?

331
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:27,510
I know.

332
00:13:28,940 --> 00:13:30,200
You had heart surgery.

333
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,260
When I first got out of prison,

334
00:13:39,570 --> 00:13:40,810
I couldn't find a job.

335
00:13:43,270 --> 00:13:45,070
I often couldn't sleep at night.

336
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:47,050
When I finally did,

337
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:48,780
I'd have nightmares.

338
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:50,420
I dreamt of Qima'er Gold Mine.

339
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:52,020
There was blood everywhere.

340
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,260
I kept thinking, if only

341
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,920
I hadn't returned to the team,

342
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:57,720
then none of this

343
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,920
would have happened.

344
00:14:00,430 --> 00:14:01,540
But I always thought of

345
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,470
Captain Duojie.

346
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,800
I felt like he was watching me.

347
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,890
It's been 17 years.

348
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,120
I finally found the Captain.

349
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:16,910
I feel like I can finally

350
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:18,080
find some closure.

351
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:21,650
I used to always want

352
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:22,910
a permanent position.

353
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:24,250
Then I went to prison.

354
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:25,910
So a permanent position

355
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,640
is out of the question for me now.

356
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,360
Now I just want to survive.

357
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:32,100
At least watch my child grow up

358
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,100
and go to college.

359
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,680
Uncle Riga.

360
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:48,840
I'll come visit you again.

361
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,900
Be careful in the mountains.

362
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:00,780
Over the years,

363
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:03,230
you've offended too many people.

364
00:15:05,190 --> 00:15:07,390
There's a 2 million bounty on your head.

365
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:32,040
Take care of yourself.

366
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:32,720
Okay.

367
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:39,690
Sangba.

368
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,970
I found this while cleaning the basement.

369
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,770
I'm returning it to you.

370
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:52,930
You still haven't returned

371
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:53,840
that copy of "Light Weapons"

372
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,040
you borrowed from me.

373
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:58,060
I haven't finished reading it yet.

374
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,260
I want it now.

375
00:16:07,540 --> 00:16:09,470
Haven't you finished reading yet?

376
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:13,230
Mom said,

377
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:16,160
"If a pillar in the temple breaks,

378
00:16:16,530 --> 00:16:18,190
one person alone can't fix it.

379
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:20,230
Everyone must offer support

380
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:21,040
to fix it."

381
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:23,590
Bai, what do you think

382
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:25,280
people live for?

383
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:39,070
[Light Weapons]

384
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,220
Actually,

385
00:16:43,330 --> 00:16:44,240
I've never regretted

386
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,070
coming back.

387
00:16:46,430 --> 00:16:46,960
Really.

388
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,390
I know.

389
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:02,220
Go.

390
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,970
I'll head back now.

391
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:30,330
Wait.

392
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,790
In the last couple of days,

393
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:34,370
what have you police

394
00:17:34,370 --> 00:17:35,280
found out?

395
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:38,460
Well...

396
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:41,060
We're still investigating.

397
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:44,740
Does that Wu Jiang,
who came to cause trouble,

398
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:45,590
have something to do

399
00:17:45,590 --> 00:17:46,720
with this incident?

400
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,640
I heard you guys are investigating him.

401
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,000
You, you...

402
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,300
Who told you that?

403
00:17:54,930 --> 00:17:56,790
The wind on the grassland told me.

404
00:18:00,690 --> 00:18:01,700
I see.

405
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:03,110
Do you go to that karaoke bar

406
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:04,180
a lot?

407
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,900
The owner has a big mouth.

408
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:09,940
Bai,

409
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:10,890
we all

410
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,090
go there often.

411
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:12,840
Quite often.

412
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:14,590
What have you found?

413
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:15,180
Tell us.

414
00:18:15,380 --> 00:18:16,960
Regarding the investigation details,

415
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:17,540
I can't

416
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:18,640
tell you anything.

417
00:18:19,770 --> 00:18:20,080
Bai,

418
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:20,530
why do you treat us

419
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:21,330
as outsiders?

420
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,270
It's not about
being insiders or outsiders.

421
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:24,550
The police have rules.

422
00:18:24,660 --> 00:18:25,420
Rules, rules.

423
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:25,830
Cases aren't solved

424
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:26,810
by following the rules.

425
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:28,550
An organization must have discipline.

426
00:18:28,550 --> 00:18:29,240
Han,

427
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:30,950
go find a job.

428
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,810
Meet more people,

429
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,250
read between the lines,

430
00:18:34,470 --> 00:18:35,620
and socialize a bit.

431
00:18:37,810 --> 00:18:38,950
I'm not arguing with you about this.

432
00:18:38,950 --> 00:18:40,400
Shao, go start the car.

433
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:41,390
Did I argue? Did I?

434
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:41,760
No, no.

435
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:42,540
Did I?

436
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:47,660
Drive safely.

437
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,070
What did she mean?

438
00:18:56,610 --> 00:18:57,850
We were just talking nicely,

439
00:18:57,850 --> 00:18:59,140
and now, a few days later,

440
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,940
she's creating division again.

441
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:02,750
Couldn't you understand

442
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:03,940
what she meant?

443
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:07,250
She didn't say anything.

444
00:19:07,740 --> 00:19:08,810
But she also didn't tell us

445
00:19:08,810 --> 00:19:10,020
to do nothing.

446
00:19:11,270 --> 00:19:12,210
What can we do?

447
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,790
Help find clues.

448
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,760
Is that what Bai meant?

449
00:19:23,870 --> 00:19:25,720
I think that's what she meant.

450
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:30,340
Liu Haoyu, right?

451
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:31,030
You used to work

452
00:19:31,030 --> 00:19:32,170
at Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company,

453
00:19:32,170 --> 00:19:32,810
right?

454
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:34,200
Here.

455
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:34,720
Thanks.

456
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,450
These people on the list—

457
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,080
have you seen them recently?

458
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:42,400
I know most of them.

459
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,640
I haven't seen this one in a long time.

460
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,520
Maybe it's been 2 months.

461
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:46,240
Two months?

462
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:46,740
Yes, yes.

463
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,450
Two months.

464
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,010
Sir.

465
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:05,920
Hello.

466
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,900
We are
from the Municipal Public Security Bureau.

467
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:08,480
We'd like

468
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,700
to ask you something.

469
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:10,310
Okay.

470
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:12,420
Is your name Li Haiyuan?

471
00:20:12,570 --> 00:20:13,140
Yes, yes.

472
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:14,450
You used to work

473
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:15,630
at Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company?

474
00:20:15,630 --> 00:20:15,930
Yes.

475
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:17,600
That was many years ago.

476
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,620
Take a look at this file first.

477
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:37,360
Is Sangba

478
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:39,130
getting used to Chengdu?

479
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:41,020
He's not very loyal.

480
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,280
He just left like that.

481
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:44,290
He's drunk on oxygen,

482
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:46,750
saying he's sleepy all the time.

483
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:49,400
Li,

484
00:20:49,770 --> 00:20:50,640
how did you let the police

485
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:51,570
get on your tail?

486
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:53,400
What do you mean by that?

487
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,750
They are investigating a case,

488
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,480
and traced it to my old company.

489
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,770
When I was young,

490
00:20:58,930 --> 00:21:00,160
I worked there as a driver.

491
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,270
That was years ago.

492
00:21:01,980 --> 00:21:04,070
Didn't you drive trucks in Mazhi before?

493
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:04,570
Yes.

494
00:21:04,940 --> 00:21:06,000
Hongyuan Freight.

495
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:08,140
I've heard of it. Big company.

496
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:09,680
Lots of people.

497
00:21:10,610 --> 00:21:11,270
I don't know

498
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:12,350
what they are looking for.

499
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:13,790
They even asked me to recall,

500
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:14,280
well,

501
00:21:14,310 --> 00:21:15,350
the missing page,

502
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:16,390
and who was on it.

503
00:21:16,860 --> 00:21:17,880
Seriously?

504
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:19,900
Who could remember that?

505
00:21:48,230 --> 00:21:49,030
What's wrong?

506
00:21:49,050 --> 00:21:50,500
I should be asking you that.

507
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,760
What's wrong with you?

508
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,020
About the middle school,

509
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:56,400
I've asked around for you.

510
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,680
Experimental Middle School
and No. 2 Middle School

511
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:58,880
are both pretty good.

512
00:21:58,940 --> 00:21:59,680
Experimental Middle School

513
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:00,450
focuses more

514
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,520
on students'

515
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:02,110
independence.

516
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,110
They value students'

517
00:22:03,110 --> 00:22:04,310
holistic education.

518
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:05,500
No. 2 Middle School

519
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:06,900
is relatively stricter.

520
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:07,300
But

521
00:22:07,330 --> 00:22:08,610
it depends on your child.

522
00:22:08,610 --> 00:22:09,460
I think both of them

523
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:09,910
are fine.

524
00:22:09,910 --> 00:22:10,370
Thanks.

525
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:29,270
Get out!

526
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:36,110
I heard this Bai Ju

527
00:22:36,110 --> 00:22:37,160
was transferred from

528
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,820
the Mazhi County Public Security Bureau.

529
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:39,950
What did she ask you?

530
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:43,210
What else could she ask?

531
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:46,030
Asked about my routes.

532
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:48,150
Asked what cargo I hauled.

533
00:22:48,310 --> 00:22:49,640
Asked if I knew Duojie.

534
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:53,180
Anyway, I just said

535
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:54,840
what the boss taught me to say.

536
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,780
I didn't tell the whole truth,

537
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:58,710
but I couldn't tell all the lies.

538
00:22:58,930 --> 00:22:59,830
I mixed truth with lies

539
00:22:59,830 --> 00:23:01,160
and ran them in circles.

540
00:23:02,570 --> 00:23:04,430
Don't talk too much to the police.

541
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,290
If they find you once,

542
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,550
they can find you a second time.

543
00:23:10,110 --> 00:23:10,830
Mr. Meng,

544
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,390
are you afraid I have a loose tongue,

545
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,220
or are you afraid

546
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:15,140
I'll drag you down with me?

547
00:23:15,140 --> 00:23:16,310
I'm reminding you.

548
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,950
If you're smart,

549
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:20,140
you should know

550
00:23:21,210 --> 00:23:22,160
that right now,

551
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:24,540
we need to stand together,

552
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,730
not fight amongst ourselves.

553
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,750
Since it's your treat today,

554
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:40,100
I'll have to open another bottle.

555
00:23:48,310 --> 00:23:49,070
Be careful.

556
00:23:49,980 --> 00:23:52,180
Don't drink too much and mess things up.

557
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,500
Mr. Meng, have you finished?

558
00:24:03,940 --> 00:24:04,550
Shen.

559
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:06,470
Mr. Meng,

560
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,380
what's up?

561
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,410
If you want to be with Wu Jiang
for the long run,

562
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:15,450
talk some sense into him.

563
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:17,040
Success isn't just about the present,

564
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:17,660
right?

565
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,660
Thank you, Mr. Meng. I'll tell him.

566
00:24:23,110 --> 00:24:24,910
You're more sensible than he is.

567
00:24:25,330 --> 00:24:26,740
Goodbye, Mr. Meng.

568
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,400
Hello, Officer Bai.

569
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:44,720
You still owe me a meal.

570
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:49,900
Kung Pao Chicken.

571
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:51,290
That's all the dishes.

572
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:52,300
We also ordered a bottle of wine.

573
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:53,430
Please bring it out.

574
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:57,550
We have fresh squeezed

575
00:24:57,580 --> 00:24:58,440
corn juice,

576
00:24:58,550 --> 00:24:59,150
yam juice,

577
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,190
and pumpkin juice.

578
00:25:00,190 --> 00:25:01,060
Take your pick.

579
00:25:01,850 --> 00:25:03,450
No need. Just bring the wine.

580
00:25:04,850 --> 00:25:06,780
Didn't you drive here?

581
00:25:06,950 --> 00:25:07,420
Where do you get

582
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:08,590
so many questions?

583
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:12,450
Alright, alright.

584
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:13,650
We'll just drink tea.

585
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:14,840
Okay, tea is good.

586
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:26,620
That's it.

587
00:25:28,780 --> 00:25:29,810
Enjoy your meal.

588
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:45,850
What's wrong?

589
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:47,940
We don't need you here anymore.

590
00:25:47,950 --> 00:25:48,950
You can leave now.

591
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,110
Our restaurant has a rule.

592
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:52,140
In this room,

593
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,530
I have to stay and serve.

594
00:25:54,810 --> 00:25:56,670
We didn't want to sit in this room.

595
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:58,250
You insisted we

596
00:25:58,250 --> 00:25:59,070
sit in such a big room.

597
00:25:59,070 --> 00:25:59,940
Ju, since you're here...

598
00:25:59,940 --> 00:26:00,400
Get out.

599
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:05,020
Take your time eating.

600
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:06,630
Call me if you need anything.

601
00:26:10,310 --> 00:26:10,910
Let's eat.

602
00:26:12,540 --> 00:26:14,800
Your brother is quite protective of you.

603
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:16,170
If I had known,

604
00:26:16,170 --> 00:26:17,880
I would have picked a different place.

605
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,940
This place is fine.

606
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,890
It's convenient for chatting.

607
00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:22,910
Go ahead.

608
00:26:23,210 --> 00:26:24,940
What do you want to see me about?

609
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:26,810
So direct.

610
00:26:27,290 --> 00:26:27,950
Are you here

611
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:29,510
to continue the blind date?

612
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:33,920
I heard

613
00:26:34,350 --> 00:26:35,750
